        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 3:34PM CDT by NWS Memphis TN</headline>
        <description>At 334 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over McDougal, or 9 miles west of Piggott, moving
northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Piggott, Campbell, Chalk Bluff Natural Area, Malden, St. Francis,
Pollard, McDougal, Saint Francis, Glennonville, Crockett, Hickoria,
Valley Ridge, Providence, Morris State Park, Wilhelmina, Brian, Chalk
Bluff Battlefield Park, McGuires, and Townley.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
